      "type": "elementBody",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Latency is not just a technical problem — it is a perceptual one. The same 300-millisecond delay feels different depending on whether the user initiated the action, what feedback they received, and what they are expecting to happen next. This paper maps the psychology of waiting and asks what design can do at each threshold.",
